Excellent food and service; food here is prepared with great care & experience. The Tom Kha Kai seafood soup is definitely delicious and filled with plenty of seafood; squid, big shrimp, mussels, and meaty sweet scallops. I guarantee you a bowl will fill you up if you’re looking for that rich creamy Thai coconut flavor soup. My favorite main dish is Pad Thai, also with seafood! Impressive to get such great seafood this far inland! The plate for dinner or supper is enough to satisfy your hunger for Thai food! I’ve eaten here at Thai Flavors for dinner & supper several times & I’ve had the pleasure to dine here! The staff are friendly and experienced to make your dining experience with them a pleasure. Whether you live or work within the Des Moines area, or just passing through I recommend dining at Thai Flavors.

So I ordered delivery for the first time. I normally don’t like Thai delivery but decided to try it anyway. My food arrived sooner then the expected time that was given to so I was happy about that. came to thai flavors that past 2 Saturdays 11/17 & 11/24 and both times we really enjoyed it. thai flavors has the best crab rangoon in des moines. the California rolls are also delicious every time. the child in our group (12 yo) ordered black pepper chicken both times- yet tonight was more spicy for her than last. last time i got panang tofu at spicy level 3 which is perfect. however on this occasion i got red curry spicy level 3 and it was more like a 5- almost intolerable for me. server this time also didn't ask us if we wanted drinks or desserts- yet last Saturday the server was very on point & attentive. we do love the establishment- just not so much the inconsistencies. other than that, i highly recommended this place for upbeat yet classy ambience, as well as to those who are new to thai cuisine and sushi because they have american style chinese plates available as well. all the curries are delicious. ☆☆☆☆

Hidden gem in a mini mall. The outside is not so impressive, but inside is a lovely, modern, clean restaurant that was packed at lunch- so get there early.
